	abstract = {We derive dynamic optimal trading strategies that minimize the expected cost of trading a large block of equity over a ﬁxed time horizon. Speciﬁcally, given a ﬁxed block SM of shares to be executed within a ﬁxed ﬁnite number of periods ¹, and given a price-impact function that yields the execution price of an individual trade as a function of the shares traded and market conditions, we obtain the optimal sequence of trades as a function of market conditions — closed-form expressions in some cases —that minimizes the expected cost of executing MS within ¹ periods. Our analysis is extended to the portfolio case in which price impact across stocks can have an important eﬀect on the total cost of trading a portfolio. ( 1998 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.},
